<promed@promedmail.org>
[The International Committee of the OIE adopted on 20 May 2003 its
Resolution No XX, "List of FMD free countries". The list is divided into 4
sections:
1. Member Countries recognised as FMD free countries where vaccination is
not practised;
2. Member Countries recognised as FMD free countries where vaccination is
practised;
3. Member Countries having an FMD free zone where vaccination is not practised;
4. Member Countries having FMD free zones where vaccination is practised.
To see the 4 lists and their updates, the reader is referred to:
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/en_fmd.htm>. - Mod.AS]
